==English==

===Etymology===
Refers to the Fourth of July, Independence Day in the United States. The specific phrase likely originates with the song "Yankee Doodle Dandy" which opens with "''I'm a Yankee Doodle Dandy / A Yankee Doodle, do or die / A real live nephew of my [[Uncle Sam|uncle Sam]]'s / Born on the Fourth of July''".

